==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inhale
<hw>In*hale"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Inhaled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inhaling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>inhalare</ets> to
breathe upon; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>halare</ets> to breathe:
cf. F. <ets>inhaler</ets>. Cf. <er>Exhale</er>.]</ety> <def>To breathe
or draw into the lungs; to inspire; <as>as, to <ex>inhale</ex> air</as>;
-- opposed to <inv>exhale</inv>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Martin was walking forth to <qex>inhale</qex> the fresh breeze of
the evening.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>inhaled</ent>⟦br⟧
